    • Field Detail

      • connectgaps

        @Option
public Boolean connectgaps
        Determines whether or not gaps (i.e. {nan} or missing values) in the provided data arrays are connected.

      • fill

        @Option
public FillAreaEnum fill
        The area to fill with a solid color. Only NONE and TOSELF are recognized.

      • fillcolor

        @Option
public String fillcolor
        The fill color.

        Default: a half-transparent variant of the line color, marker color, or marker line color, whichever is available.

      • hovertext$array

        @Option(value="hovertext")
public String[] hovertext$array
        Hover text elements associated with each (lon,lat) pair or item in "locations" as an array of string where the items are mapped in order to the this trace's (lon,lat) or "locations" coordinates. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

      • hovertext$string

        @Option(value="hovertext")
public String hovertext$string
        Hover text elements associated with each (lon,lat) pair or item in "locations" as a single string where the same string appears over all the data points. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

      • lat

        @Option
public double[] lat
        The latitude coordinates (in degrees North).

      • line_color

        @Option(value="line.color")
public String line_color
        The line color.

      • line_width

        @Option(value="line.width")
public Integer line_width
        The line width (in px).

        Default: 2

      • lon

        @Option
public double[] lon
        The longitude coordinates (in degrees East).

      • marker

        @Option
public final MarkerOptions marker
        Options for marker.

      • mode

        @Option
public String mode
        Any combination of "lines", "markers", "text" joined with a "+" OR "none". examples: "lines", "markers", "lines+markers", "lines+markers+text", "none" default: "markers" Determines the drawing mode for this scatter trace. If the provided "mode" includes "text" then the "text" elements appear at the coordinates. Otherwise, the "text" elements appear on hover.

      • selected

        @Option
public final SelectedOptions selected

      • subplot

        @Option
public String subplot
        Reference between this trace's data coordinates and a mapbox subplot. If "mapbox" (the default value), the data refer to "layout.mapbox". If "mapbox2", the data refer to "layout.mapbox2", and so on.

      • text$array

        @Option(value="text")
public String[] text$array
        Text elements associated with each (lon,lat) pair or item in "locations" as an array of string where the items are mapped in order to the this trace's (lon,lat) or "locations" coordinates. If trace "hoverinfo" contains a "text" flag and "hovertext" is not set, these elements will be seen in the hover labels.

      • text$string

        @Option(value="text")
public String text$string
        Text elements associated with each (lon,lat) pair or item in "locations" as a single string where the same string appears over all the data points. If trace "hoverinfo" contains a "text" flag and "hovertext" is not set, these elements will be seen in the hover labels.

      • textfont

        @Option
public final FontOptions textfont
        The text font.

      • textposition

        @Option
public TextPositionEnum textposition
        The positions of the "text" elements with respects to the (x,y) coordinates.

        Default: TOP_CENTER

      • unselected

        @Option
public final SelectedOptions unselected
